<paragraph blockId="19.[178,1085,1294,1377]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet 
<emphasis box="[590,718,1294,1315]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532">undulicornis</emphasis>
is a Latin compound name derived from 
<emphasis box="[235,286,1325,1346]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532">unda</emphasis>
(= wave) and 
<emphasis box="[438,497,1325,1346]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532">cornu</emphasis>
(= horn). I refer to the undulation of the anterior margin of antennomere 9.
</paragraph>
